RACE.RACE_TEXT: PRAIRIE MEADOWS RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 82. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 17300. FOR THREE YEAR OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $5,000 OR LESS SINCE JUNE 16, 2022 OR CLAIMING $10,000. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since March 16, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (R aces Where Entered For $10,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: OURBESTFRIEND D L advanced to engage CHICAGO CHROME for the lead nearing the half mile marker, vied three deep around the turn, hustled along into stretch run, dug in under firm handling and kicked clear. POP'S BISCUIT tracked the embattled trio into the turn, swung four wide into the lane, responded under right handed pressure and produced a solid finish. CHICAGO CHROME sped to the lead at the start, took on the challenge from outside duo nearing the half mile marker, vied for command along the inside around the turn, fought back in upper stretch then flattened in late stages. HACKER roused forward to engage rivals for the lead mid-way near the half mile marker, dueled between rivals around the turn, sustained bid into upper stretch then gave way. DRINK lacked speed and raced in the back, chased four wide around the turn and failed to move into contention.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PRAIRIE MEADOWS RACE 2 1M Dirt CR: 49. Maiden Claiming Purse 22015. FOR REGISTERED STATE BRED MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: THE AWFUL TRUTH was allowed to settle out of the gate, raced two to three wide into the first turn, remained unhurried in the back up the backstretch, edged closer late on the far turn, given cue four wide at the head of the lane, responded willingly, rallied through the stretch run and surged by late. RUDY TOOTY dueled for the lead along the inside around the first turn, continued to battle for command up the backstretch, shook free leaving the quarter pole, widened to a clear advantage in upper stretch, continued clear into the final furlong then got caught late. MOLLY BYE O dueled three deep around the first turn and up the backstretch, could not match strides for the lead late on the far turn and steadily weakened. KAMEA dueled between rivals around the turn and up the backstretch, could not maintain equal terms past the midway point on the far turn and steadily faded. MY FOUR POINT OH was well placed tracking the embattled trio up the backstretch, came under a ride two to three wide around the far turn, swung wider for the drive and retreated.

ENTRY.COMMENT: unhurried, edged closer late turn, 4wd bid 3/16, rallied, up late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PRAIRIE MEADOWS RACE 3 1M Dirt CR: 89. Claiming Purse 20400. FOR THREE YEAR OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE JUNE 16, 2022. Claiming Price $30,000 (Races Where Entered For $25,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DOUBLE THUNDER stalked the pace near the inside up the backstretch, made a move along the inside with three furlongs left to run, dueled with TEMPTED MISSION around the far turn, shook free to a slim lead in upper stretch, kept under steady urging and held clear. TEMPTED MISSION took over the lead entering the first turn and angled inside, set the pace up the backstretch, dueled with DOUBLE THUNDER around the far turn, could not match strides in upper stretch but stayed on with good effort to finish clearly second best. JOHN R lacked speed and raced well off the early leaders, swung three wide into the lane, showed run in final furlong and gained a share. GRAZEN IN THE PARK raced off the early pace, came under a ride along the inside at the head of the lane, showed some mild interest and improved position. HUNKA BURNING LOVE broke on top then conceded position to TEMPTED MISSION soon after the start, stalked rival up the backstretch, came under a ride mid-way around the far turn, failed to respond and steadily faded through the lane. BUZZER raced in range three to four wide up the backstretch, failed to advance under pressure around the far turn and retreated in the lane.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PRAIRIE MEADOWS RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 72. Claiming Purse 17807. FOR REGISTERED STATE BRED THREE YEAR OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE IN 2023. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NOT ROCKET SCIENCE rated off the embattled trio up the backstretch, edged closer late on the turn, given cue three to four wide at the top of the lane, responded willingly, surged to confront OSCAR WINNER WALLY in the final sixteenth, gained a slim lead and edged away. OSCAR WINNER WALLY dueled for the lead along the inside in opening stages and continued to battle up the backstretch, shook free mid-way around the turn, widened advantage in upper stretch, continued to lead the way under steady encouragement then got overtaken in deep stretch. A BRUSH OF LUCK rated off the early pace, saved ground around the turn, shifted out four wide entering the lane, responded when called upon and captured show. SHUT UP MAN dueled three deep in opening stages, battled for command up the backstretch, chased three wide around the turn, sustained bid into upper stretch then lacked closing response and lost show. MY BOBBY MCGEE raced in the back through early stages, swung four wide into the lane and showed response in deep stretch. GIANT GAMBLE dueled between rivals up the backstretch, ran on two wide around the turn then tired in the drive.
